# Dispatch background-phase posture

## Staleness classifier (R32)

Before escalating a background phase as stuck, run the multi-signal staleness classifier
(`scripts/phase_staleness_lib.py`) with last tool-call, last commit, last status write, and
`pendingHumanReply`. Defer watchdog timeout when classification is `waiting-on-human` at high/medium
confidence; treat `genuinely-stuck` at high confidence as a legitimate halt candidate. Intra-phase Task
dispatch remains disabled — classification does not introduce a new dispatch path.


Background phase sub-agents disable intra-phase Task dispatch — inline two-stage review only (R45).
